 3

). In the subgroup analysis of droplet‐transmitted infections, compared to the control arm, the efficacy of continuous N95 respirators against droplet‐transmitted infections (bacterial and viral) was 74% (RR 0.26, 95% CI 0.16‐0.42) and 57% in the targeted N95 arm (RR 0.43, 95% CI 0.25‐0.72) (Table

 4

).

